<br>
Pulling is challenging, Lull is resisted frequently and 5-6 lull attempts in a row isn't uncommon. Charisma is your friend to avoid agro on resisted lulls, Bards always use Charisma song unless you are WAY high on Charisma. Leave some pulling room between you and your group so an agro doesn't automaticly wipe you all out heh. Con the mobs before lulling, and go for blue ones first. If you get a lot of resists in a row try a different mobs, some are harder to lull than others.<br>
<br>
Mez lands but is resisted a bit as well. You definitely do not want to try to keep 3+ mobs mezed. At times it might be beneficial to pull with Mez instead of Lull, and it isn't worth the time to single pull. Get doubles and mez. Snare is a MUST!<br>
